<headline>Winter Weather Advisory issued December 31 at 1:21PM MST until December 31 at 8:00PM MST by NWS Boise</headline>
<description>...WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 8 PM MST THIS
EVENING...
* WHAT...Snow and blowing snow. Additional snow accumulations of
up to 2 inches, mainly in the mountains. Wind gusts to 30 mph
will cause areas of blowing and drifting snow.
* WHERE...Owyhee Mountains and Southwest Highlands zones.
* WHEN...Until 8 PM MST this evening.
* IMPACTS...Travel could be difficult. Areas of blowing snow
could significantly reduce visibility.</description>
<instruction>Slow down and use caution while traveling.
The latest road conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1.</instruction>
